<br>
I still think they should have given several either/or ability choices to classes that are shared between realms. This would have allowed for personal customisation rather then just defining each class further with a skill only that class had. That would soon sort out the better realm skills and no one could complain about fixing the weaker ones.<br>
<br>
For example: Minstrels, Skalds and Bards would all get to choose to buy *one of* SoS, FoG, and the Bards uber healing chant. Of course that'd mean all Skalds and Bards would have SoS as well as Minstrels, which would make it obvious to Mythic that the other two are just not up to par. They could then nerf SoS and/or boost the others and no one could really complain (providing those with SoS got a RS respec if it got nerfed).<br>
<br>
Once all three are up to par you'd have a lot more individuality per character rather then having all members of each class (well certain classes anyway, and I feel we are one of those) being virtual duplicates.<br>
<br>
As well as the class clone syndrome the current set up makes it hard to fix poor realm abilities because it's seen as loving/nerfing towards specific classes rather then to a broken/gimped ability. At the moment Skalds are still falsely considered overpowered and that will unfortunatly mean we will probably never get the fixes we need. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=nattfari>Nattfari</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 9<br> <font color=#ff0000>(12/26/02 1:45:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=408.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Skald Report as posted - Read closely!</span><hr size=1> Very nice report as usually.  Although I must say that I wish that more emhasis would be put on our melee/defense skills than our support skills.<br>
